Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Brown meat with onions in large skillet on medium-high heat; drain. Stir in next 4 ingredients. Place 3 tortillas in single layer on bottom of 13x9-inch baking dish. Cover with layers of half each of the meat mixture, sour cream and cheese. Repeat layers; cover. Bake 40 minutes or until casserole is heated through and cheese is melted, uncovering after 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.